  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "We are working on the support of AuRa consensus in Erigon, and some initial work has been done by @AskAlexSharov to support Sokol POA network. This work needs to continue.\r\n\r\nIn AuRa, block headers have an extra field, called \"Seal\", which does not appear in any non-AuRa network. This `Seal` field contains the block number signed by the validator who \"approved\", or \"sealed\" that block. In the current version of code in `devel` branch, there is no verification of that signature. This verification needs to be added and Stage \"Headers\" needs to report error and abort if the signature is invalid.",
